<p>Eben Moglen, Executive Director of the SFLC, testified at the Congressional <a href="http://energycommerce.house.gov/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2147:hearing-on-do-not-track-legislation-is-now-the-right-time&catid=129:subcommittee-on-commerce-trade-and-consumer-protection&Itemid=70">“Do-Not-Track Legislation: Is Now the Right Time?”</a> hearing held in Washington D.C. on December 2nd.</p>

<p>Eben's prepared testimony is available from <a href="http://www.softwarefreedom.org/events/2010/do-not-track/Eben-Moglen-2010-12-2-privacy-testimony.pdf">our site</a> (pdf) while video of the entire hearing is available <a href="http://www.c-spanvideo.org/program/NotTr">from C-Span</a>.</p>

<p>As per the committee's invitation, Eben submitted the following <a href="http://www.softwarefreedom.org/events/2010/do-not-track/Eben-Moglen-revised-privacy-testimony.pdf">revised testimony</a> (pdf).</p>

